<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Shell on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/shell/</link><description>Recent content in Shell on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/shell/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C system() Deprecated — Replace with exec Family</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/system/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/c/system/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-system-deprecated--replace-with-exec-family"&gt;[Solution] C system() Deprecated — Replace with exec Family&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;system()&lt;/code&gt; function is deprecated in secure coding guidelines because it invokes a shell to execute commands, making it vulnerable to shell injection attacks. If any part of the command string comes from user input, an attacker can inject arbitrary commands. The safe replacement is the &lt;code&gt;exec&lt;/code&gt; family of functions, which execute programs directly without a shell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compiler warnings with security flags:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Docker Exec Error — Fix Container Exec Failures</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-docker-exec-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-docker-exec-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="docker-exec-error--fix-container-exec-failures"&gt;Docker Exec Error — Fix Container Exec Failures&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Docker exec error occurs when &lt;code&gt;docker exec&lt;/code&gt; fails to run a command inside a running container. The error reads:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Error: No such container: &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;exec failed: unable to start container process: exec: &amp;quot;sh&amp;quot;: executable file not found in $PATH&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;docker exec&lt;/code&gt; creates a new process inside an existing running container. It requires the container to be in a running state and the specified command or shell to exist in the container&amp;rsquo;s filesystem. Common failures include the container not running, the shell not being installed, or permission issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS Terminal.app Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-terminal-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-terminal-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-terminalapp-error-fix"&gt;macOS Terminal.app Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Terminal errors include Terminal not launching, blank or garbled screen, crashes on startup, or shell sessions not responding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Terminal.app hosts shell sessions (zsh by default). Errors can be in the Terminal app itself, the shell configuration, or the TERM environment settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupt Terminal preferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shell initialization script has errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TERM environment variable misconfigured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Terminal process limit reached&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupt terminal emulation database&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-reset-terminal-preferences"&gt;1. Reset Terminal preferences&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults delete com.apple.Terminal
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-check-shell-configuration"&gt;2. Check shell configuration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Test if .zshrc has syntax errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;zsh -n ~/.zshrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Start a clean shell session&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;zsh --no-rcs
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-fix-term-environment-variable"&gt;3. Fix TERM environment variable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;export TERM&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;xterm-256color
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;export TERM=xterm-256color&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.zshrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-check-terminal-database"&gt;4. Check terminal database&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;infocmp xterm-256color
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;brew install ncurses &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# via Homebrew if missing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-apple-script-error"&gt;AppleScript Error&lt;/a&gt; - AppleScript execution errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-homebrew-error"&gt;Homebrew Error&lt;/a&gt; - package manager issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-syntax-error"&gt;Bash Syntax Error&lt;/a&gt; - shell syntax issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] VBA Shell: process start error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/vba/vba-shell-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/vba/vba-shell-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VBA Shell function errors occur when the operating system cannot execute a command, the executable doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, or there are permission issues launching external processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executable file doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Command path contains spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient permissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid command syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;32-bit vs 64-bit compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Antivirus blocking execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; WRONG: Path with spaces not quoted
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub Example1()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Shell &amp;#34;C:\Program Files\App\app.exe&amp;#34; &amp;#39; Error: spaces in path
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; CORRECT: Quote paths with spaces
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub Example1()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Shell &amp;#34;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&amp;#34; &amp;amp; &amp;#34;C:\Program Files\App\app.exe&amp;#34; &amp;amp; &amp;#34;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;, vbNormalFocus
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; WRONG: No error handling
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub Example2()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim pid As Double
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; pid = Shell(&amp;#34;notepad.exe&amp;#34;, vbNormalFocus)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &amp;#39; May fail if not found
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; CORRECT: Handle errors and wait
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub Example2()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim pid As Double
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; On Error GoTo ErrHandler
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; pid = Shell(&amp;#34;notepad.exe&amp;#34;, vbNormalFocus)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; If pid = 0 Then
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; MsgBox &amp;#34;Failed to start process&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Exit Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; End If
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &amp;#39; Wait for process to complete (optional)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &amp;#39; WaitForProcess pid
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Exit Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ErrHandler:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; MsgBox &amp;#34;Error: &amp;#34; &amp;amp; Err.Description
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; CORRECT: Use WMI for more control
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub Example3()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim wmi As Object
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim processes As Object
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Set wmi = GetObject(&amp;#34;winmgmts:\\.\root\cimv2&amp;#34;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Set processes = wmi.Get(&amp;#34;Win32_Process&amp;#34;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim result As Variant
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; result = processes.Create(&amp;#34;notepad.exe&amp;#34;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; If result = 0 Then
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; MsgBox &amp;#34;Process started successfully&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Else
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; MsgBox &amp;#34;Failed to start process: &amp;#34; &amp;amp; result
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; End If
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;#39; CORRECT: Wait for process to complete
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sub WaitForProcess(pid As Long)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim wmi As Object
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dim process As Object
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Set wmi = GetObject(&amp;#34;winmgmts:\\.\root\cimv2&amp;#34;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Do
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Set process = wmi.Get(&amp;#34;Win32_Process.ProcessId=&amp;#34; &amp;amp; pid)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; If process Is Nothing Then Exit Do
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; DoEvents
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Sleep 100
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Loop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;End Sub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="vba-file-not-found-v2"&gt;File Not Found&lt;/a&gt; - missing executables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="vba-permission-denied-v2"&gt;Permission Denied&lt;/a&gt; - access issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="vba-adodb-connection-error"&gt;ADO Connection Error&lt;/a&gt; - database access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>